#19602
Chamber of Dedication~
This vast, cavernous room is the focal point of the monks' humble
subordinance to their deity.  Lines of pews, crafted of dark ebonwood
and surfaced with beaten gold, await the arrival of worshipping
acolytes.  At the far end of the room, you can barely make out a sort
of floating platform, adorned with a lavish altar and positioned
high enough in the air to be visible from all corners of the chamber.
~
