#19611
The Armoury~
  The smell of molten iron greets you as you enter the monastery's 
armoury.  From the rear of the steaming chamber, the monotonous tone
of a dwarven hammer striking steel pounds into your skull.  Scattered
about the room are the remnants of shields and armour obviously not up
to the smith's ridiculously high standards.  Various suits of mail also
lie here, polished to a pristine shine, and waiting to be worn into 
battle.
  The hammering here is echoed by the sound of another forger plying his
trade to the south.
~
