#19626
Northern Dining Hall~
  This luxuriously appointed dining hall is restricted to those of
significant power in the priesthood.  A massive chandelier, formed of
thousands of softly glowing crystals, provides breath-taking 
illumination.  Large oaken tables, immaculately polished to a pristine
shine, are situated throughout the room, surrounded by elegantly carved,
velvet backed chairs.
  The smells and noises of wondrous food being prepared issue from the
swinging doors to the south.
~
