Southern Dining Hall~
  This austere room is the mess-hall of the acolytes and common priests
in the citadel.  Long wooden benches and tables, well-made and practical,
occupy most of the room.  Bowls of steaming gruel and mugs of bitter tea
are being served by culinary servants rushing in through swinging doors
to the north.  The gruel, while hardly delicious, is highly nutritious,
and is being lapped up by the lowly monks with obvious fervor.
~
